Definition: a slow kind of alcoholic fermentation at a temperature low enough that the yeast cells can sink to the bottom of the fermenting liquid
Example: used in the production of lager
Synonyms: zymosis, a, slow, kind, of, alcoholic, fermentation, at, temperature, low, enough, that, the, yeast, cells, can, sink, to, bottom, fermenting, liquid, used, in, production, lager
Category: noun.process
